summary: This document outlines the terms and conditions for the issuance of Series A and Series B asset-backed Commercial Paper Notes by Micawber Co., LLC. It details the structure of the notes, liquidity agreements, payment priorities, and investment policies, as well as the roles of various parties involved in the transaction.
keyFacts: The document describes the issuance of Series A and Series B asset-backed Commercial Paper Notes by Micawber Co., LLC.
The Series A Notes are senior to the Series B Notes in terms of payment priority.
A liquidity facility provided by the Federal Reserve is available to support the Series A Notes.
The Company is organized as a bankruptcy-remote limited liability company under Delaware law.
The document outlines investment policies and restrictions regarding the purchase of assets to back the Commercial Paper Notes.
